This is a list of the 50 most significant science fiction/fantasy novels, 1953-2002, according to the Science Fiction Book Club. Bold the ones you've read, strike-out the ones you hated, italicize those you started but never finished and put an asterisk beside the ones you loved.

1. The Lord of the Rings, J.R.R. Tolkien
2. The Foundation Trilogy, Isaac Asimov
3. Dune, Frank Herbert
4. Stranger in a Strange Land, Robert A. Heinlein
5. A Wizard of Earthsea, Ursula K. Le Guin*
6. Neuromancer, William Gibson
7. Childhood's End, Arthur C. Clarke
8. Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?, Philip K. Dick
9. The Mists of Avalon, Marion Zimmer Bradley
10. Fahrenheit 451, Ray Bradbury
11. The Book of the New Sun, Gene Wolfe
12. A Canticle for Leibowitz, Walter M. Miller, Jr.
13. The Caves of Steel, Isaac Asimov
14. Children of the Atom, Wilmar Shiras
15. Cities in Flight, James Blish
16. The Colour of Magic, Terry Pratchett
17. Dangerous Visions, edited by Harlan Ellison
18. Deathbird Stories, Harlan Ellison
19. The Demolished Man, Alfred Bester
20. Dhalgren, Samuel R. Delany
21. Dragonflight, Anne McCaffrey
22. Ender's Game, Orson Scott Card*
23. The First Chronicles of Thomas Covenant the Unbeliever, Stephen R. Donaldson
24. The Forever War, Joe Haldeman
25. Gateway, Frederik Pohl
26. Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone, J.K. Rowling
27. The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy, Douglas Adams*
28. I Am Legend, Richard Matheson
29. Interview with the Vampire, Anne Rice
30. The Left Hand of Darkness, Ursula K. Le Guin
31. Little, Big, John Crowley
32. Lord of Light, Roger Zelazny
33. The Man in the High Castle, Philip K. Dick
34. Mission of Gravity, Hal Clement
35. More Than Human, Theodore Sturgeon
36. The Rediscovery of Man, Cordwainer Smith
37. On the Beach, Nevil Shute
38. Rendezvous with Rama, Arthur C. Clarke
39. Ringworld, Larry Niven
40. Rogue Moon, Algis Budrys
41. The Silmarillion, J.R.R. Tolkien
42. Slaughterhouse-5, Kurt Vonnegut
43. Snow Crash, Neal Stephenson
44. Stand on Zanzibar, John Brunner
45. The Stars My Destination, Alfred Bester
46. Starship Troopers, Robert A. Heinlein
47. Stormbringer, Michael Moorcock
48. The Sword of Shannara, Terry Brooks
49. Timescape, Gregory Benford

Sort of behind on certain things

I know, I know, we're down two games to none. It's been a difficult last two nights as I have watched my ball club beat themselves. Sure the Tigers are playing well, but we are not capitalizing on the MANY scoring opportunities presented to us at this time. Hell, in game one we set an LCS record for the most double plays in a game with Runners in scoring position. If we lose this series we need to learn one thing from this, we need SPEED. We need people on the bases who are a stealing threat, that changes how the other team has to play us and should lower the double plays.

Though my team's lack of culmination is not the only thing that has been depressing me this week, there are just so many other things to choose from aren't there. From the right-wing trying and praying to find SOME way to pin this entire Foley thing on the Democrats to the media and their lack of chasing any REAL story, it is getting ludicrous.

Now Faux News has tried labeling Foley a Democrat on the O'Reily Shitter, they have attempted to change this into a homosexuality debate, and now they try to pin it on the shoulders of Democrats. A Congressman from North Carolina recently was being grilled about the Foley case and he tried o suggest the Democratic leadership knew about this. When Wolf asked if he had any proof that they knew about Foley his response was, "Do you have any evidence that they didn't know?!" It goes without saying he was a Republican, course he also looked like that little kid who always followed around the bigger kids cause he thought that made him cool too.

Hannity of course tries to link McGreevy to this because he liked to have sex with strange men. Of course he did, can we really expect anything less at this point from that assclown? Luckily John Walsh, a true patriot and great American, was there to put him in his place.

I find that this action is absolutely disgusting. You have a Navy Lawyer who is able to win a Supreme Court case and you don't promote him because the Administration had some dirt kicked in their face? Pure garbage, political bullshit and there is no place in America for it. I for one salute the Lt. Commander for his time served and for doing his job to the best of his ability.

The more and more Keith Olbermann goes on, the more and more I believe he is becoming the best political commentator in his time. Sure Colbert and Stewart are good, but they capture us with comedy gold and can't cover as nearly as many subject as KO can. Though on occasion the former ESPN Anchor can give us comedy gold in the form of sarcasm as well.

Last night, Anita and I got into a discussion about the media and what stories they chose to run and the ones they let fall by the wayside. Apparently there is an entire organization that covers just these type of events. I brought up such points of the media not caring about school shootings, unless they are in white suburbia, not the inner city. How they no longer truly report, they merely do what sells. The saddest part of all of this equation is the American people, the consumer, who have this unnatural need for celebrity gossip and stories that affect none of our lives. It absolutely disgusts the writer and report within me.

Finally I want to end on a note that is not political in nature. As many know who read this I am an avid pro wrestling viewer, it is one of my passions in life. Hell, I even commentate once a month (next weekend come out to Glen Burnie for the EWA ) and I have a blast doing so. I watched the Raw "Family Reunion" this last Monday and I have a few thoughts on the state of the WWE Product.

Raw, I can enjoy about half of it right now. The DX reunion puts me to sleep half of the time, though they have been pretty hilarious lately. Giving Jeff Hardy, a sloppy worker in my opinion, the IC title so quickly is a mistake. Make him chase the title, Nitro and Melina were perfect for the IC title scene. The tag team division is disgustingly awful on Raw and needs to be fixed in a hurry. John Cena, he can be funny, but if I see one more push for The Marine I might lose it. I am excited to see Cryme Tyme though, that has been a highlight in recent weeks.

Smackdown, does anyone actually still watch this show? The saddest thing of all, the majority of the workers in the WWE who I am a fan of are on this show. Hardy, Gibson, Jimmy, Helms, Benoit, Regal, London, Kendrick, and MISTER KENNEDY. Sadly though, the booking is so atrocious and they never let any of the undercard show their talent it has become unwatchable. True, I get a kick out of the whole King Booker gimmick, I think he really flung himself into the role and it is really amusing, I would just love to see it show more action.

Then we come to the rebirth of ECW. Naturally this is my favorite WWE program, and not just for the Diva Strip Poker. As we can tell by the picture above they have the best thing going for them right now, CM Punk. Kevin Thorn and Ariel have been an enjoyment, least for me, to watch, Punk has stolen ECW. He is easily the most popular wrestler week to week on ECW. Hell, until we see him with REAL competition we may never know if he is their best worker, but as of right now he might be the most consistent worker the WWE has.

In closing, it was nice to see Piper and Money Inc on Raw, but the real pleasure of the night was Arn Anderson. He may have received the biggest pop of the night, but you saw all those fours in the air. Hell, I won't even lie, when I heard the greatest theme music ever in wrestling even my hands were in the air, and that's no lie.

All I'm going to say is this

Mal/Caleb has been cast as a character on Lost!

So I was writing this earlier when Blogger did something funky and eliminated the ENTIRE thing, which was a lengthy post too. Pissed me off a little bit because there were really good links for all you faithful people and now my lazy ass has to go out and find them once more, damn annoying. To start off like I did the last one that is the image of Green Arrow for the Smallville Halloween episode, damn money if you ask me. Not only is Green Arrow on for the majority of the season one episode, entitled Justice, will include Aquaman, Cyborg and The Flash. Yeah, second episode in Jan will be fucking money. I haven't updated lately because my plate is full, hell, it's overflowing with awesomeness. This past Saturday saw another day and another commentary goldmine for me and the EWA. I think it will be a first in commentating history to mention Golden Showers, the Paris Hilton sex tape, illiteracy, sexual favors, men screwing other men, virginity and...baby powder. I cannot wait for this show to come out on DVD, hopefully before this time next year. I have also begun DJing at The Swerve at Kellys Irish Times in DC next to Union Station. What began as helping out during the kickball nights has now grown into a full-fledged job, interesting how things like that happen. Now I know must wonder how one such as I can put up with crappy request after crappy request after Journey request, but hey, the money is good and I usually drink for free. I don't have a set night as of yet, but give it time, I might just. Hell, I am probably working there the next few weekends if people get bored. Anita is, well to put it simply, amazing. She is without a doubt the best there is, the best there was and probably the best there ever will be in my life. I don't know what I did right karma wise to be blessed with such an amazing woman but I have been and I will cherish her for as long as I am allowed. For the first time in my life I'm not thinking about what could have been, what should have been and wondering why it wasn't. All I'm thinking about is the future and spending it with her. Hell, apparently I was the talk of the weekend at her parent's place this weekend. Note to self, make sure to bug her before her next visit so I can listen in to said conversation. Bill Clinton recently did a sit down interview with a Faux News lackey and per usual the Faux News Lackey went from talking about the Clinton Global Imitative, something truly remarkable and likely to get him the Nobel Prize, and of course they attack how he did "Nothing to capture Bin Laden.". FINALLY he stands up to the lackey and lays down the FACTS about the 90s and what HE attempted to do with opposition from the Republican Party. Now, I wish I could link the videos for you to watch (I myself have watched it a few times today alone) but Fox News has already attacked YouTube and ordered that they take DOWN the videos. I guess they took their ball and ran home, fucking pussies. I CAN NOT WAIT to watch the Daily Show tonight as this was aired yesterday morning on Faux. Damn, even the Saturday spot where they try to already spin the interview BEFORE it is even aired has been taken down. You should be ashamed of yourself Faux News. If this was Dubya and another glory piece you'd let everyone and their mothers post it up, but since it is Bubba slicing your balls off and making earrings for you, it must come down. I can truly now see that it is fair and balanced. Along the same lines, a new documentary has debuted and it is one I strongly suggest you all go out and see. Iraq For Sale is done by the same gentleman who brought us the documentaries about Wal-Mart and Faux News. They are not releasing this to theaters, all money for the project was raised through the internet, and all showings are going to be done by groups. I myself am planning on going to the October 8th showing in DC if Anita feels so inclined and not in Houston. I urge you all to do the same, and to get out and vote in November so we can take back the House and Senate. Finally today the big news in the wrestling world this weekend is that the first MAJOR shot was issued across the bow of the USS WWE. Kurt F'N Angle has signed on with TNA. Not only has he signed on with TNA, TNA has been given a PRIME TIME SLOT on Spike TV (9pm on Thursdays in Mid-November). Christian was one thing, his contract expired and he moved on to where he can be a star. KURT ANGLE is and has been arguably the best wrestler in the world since 2002. Kurt leaving Vince to sign with TNA truly means they actually MEAN something in the wrestling industry in the US. Christian was one thing, he was a mid-carder someone I'm sure Vince saw as expendable, but this is Kurt F'N Angle. No more of, you will only see an Olympic Gold Medalist here, now we will only see him on TNA.

It has been quite some time since I wrote anything hasn't it? I mean the last meaningful post I made was post Rollins Band and as much as I wish I could claim that the absence was due to post-Rollins come-down, it has not been. Of course I have been informed by my lawyer that I can not use her as an excuse...for anything. But quickly, you may wonder why I have this picture of Claudio Castagnoli up right now. Well, last night watching Raw there he was, the man from the Swiss Banks himself, playing a cop behind Shane-O-Mac. That's right, Claudio Castagnoli made a Raw appearance. So, sorry no more side stories until I get this one out of the way. Yes, the reason I have been MIA lately is that I have met someone. Now I cannot confirm nor deny that they are the said lawyer above all I can say is that this person or persons are brilliant, sexy, gorgeous, and cynical and most importantly a Browns fan. Now, her and her friends don't like their real names being used due to their positions so I have come up with a name for her on this blog. As she loves stuffed animals, coffee and is as cynical as anyone I have ever met her name from here on out on this blog will be Anita. Anita and I met through a common kickball friend who had been trying to get this accomplished for a few weeks. When we all finally went out together, her mission was complete...but ours was far from over. We then proceeded to turn this friend into...basically...Beaker. For those of you who are not familiar with the Beaker name here is a lil visual aid. Needless to say seeing Anita and the Joker kissing and making comments about things that will not be named here definitely turned Beaker's brain to mush, though I'm sure the alcohol did not help either. So yes, that is where I have been at the last 2.5-4 weeks, depending on whose calendar you're going off of. Hell, I haven't seen my bedroom for longer then an hour on most of those days. Get your mind out of the gutters, it isn't like that, we just really enjoy each other's company. No, I am not kidding I don't care what you think you know about me. You could bet money right now on that and would owe me MILLIONS, nay, BILLIONS! So yes, I am very happy at this moment in time and it isn't just the coffee either. For all you Faire going folk, if you're brave enough to challenge the possible tropical storm that may or may not hit us this weekend we shall be attending buying her first garb...ever. I hope it isn't raining too badly, I was going to wear my kilt to the faire. In other news, Stacey moves in this Sunday to much fanfare. She will be the first to tell you that what she expected was nothing close to what was actually there in our apartment. It is not the party capital, orgy central you all may think it is. Hell, if she's reading this, she's going to be introduced to everyone on Sunday if we get her moved in quickly enough. We're having a BBQ at a friend's place on Sunday and I'll have to drag her along. Well, that is it folks. My roommates wonder if I'm alive, my Xbox 360 misses me, Anita's cat LOVES me much to her hatred. Faire this Saturday, hopefully, BBQ Sunday, up-close and personal with Albert Puljos on Tuesday and then the football season starts, cash money mudda facko.

Last night in DC there were two events I really wanted to go to. One would be the one everyone would probably assume I would go to, the Smackdown and ECW tapings. You have Sabu vs Rob Van Dam in a ladder match, CM Punk wrestling and appearances by Mick Foley and Ric Flair, my favorite and the greatest wrestlers of all time. People who knew me would think this would be a forgone conclusion that I would be at ECW.

I was even planning on going when they first announced the show, but then I found out about ANOTHER show. Last night I attended a show that I more or less imagine is what church feels like to the religious right. I went and saw ROLLINS BAND LIVE. Even though it was held in a location, the 9:30 Club, that has outlawed any fun of any kind by the audience, read no real mosh pits. I mean, I saw some kind who looked like he belonged at a REM show in the middle of the pit and NOT A SOUL TOOK HIM OUT! Doing his crappy ass pop punk mosh jump, I just wanted to go into it elbow him like my name was Dusty and then curb stomp the fucktard.

That was the saddest part, cause Henry and the band were fuckin ON last night. I had my blood pumping more then any time I can remember in recent memory. Henry may be 40 now, but can still out rock any person on the planet, save for Iggy Pop apparently. Speaking of Iggy Pop, I want a DNA test on the lead singer of The Riverboat Gamblers, the opening band. Not only did he look a lil too much like Iggy, but he had that vast amount of energy, even climbing into the balcony to hit on a chick stage left. The band, pretty good, I enjoyed their shit. They played well; songs were nice and definitely had the energy for the stage.

He was good, though he was no Henry. No one else in the world comes out in only black shorts, no shirt no shoes, and nothing but pure adrenaline. Im pretty sure John Cena wishes he was Hank; he tries to emulate him enough when hes in the ring. If youve never had the pleasure to see Henry live, be it spoken word or concert, I highly recommend it. I know Eric will be jealous of me for getting to see Liar LIVE. I think I can honestly say that Rollins Band and Clan An Drumma are neck and neck for best concert I have ever seen.

I know its been a few days since my last post, even after I proclaimed that I would attempt to write on a daily basis. Well, I wish I could say I had a good excuse for the lack of updates. I mean the weekend doesnt count, the other days yeah I should have an excuse and maybe I do. I met someone Friday night; its as simple as that. Shes amazing and things have been very nice the last few days. Dont ask questions, I wont answer them. Were merely enjoying each others company and the ride it is taking us on.

Today is a good day as well for my X-Box 360 will be there when I arrive home tonight. I already turned in my former X-box games and used those to purchase Call of Duty 2 GOTY Edition. With the tax check here I can go forward with my next ink which is LONG overdue. As of right now I am planning on my fremen text across my back but if that turns out to be too expensive then I may just go right to the Gonzo fist on my right forearm. Hell, if that isn't too expensive then I'll move to the left forearm and get my V for Vendetta logo as well. No other news other then...well...my life could get VERY interesting around the middle of July. If things keep progressing the way they are in all areas, I'm going to be killed. What is it in reference to? Well, to be frank, it means I would have a hard time keeping position in HGWCGD.

So to keep all of you informed as many do not know yet, I have my first date in a long time tonight. This is a real first date first date, something I don't know if I've done in years. We've had zero kind of hook up and have been friends for just over a year now. She's a kickballer, beautiful, and one of those ladies who are just "cool as hell". Naturally I am a bit nervous about tonight cause as of right now I have zero clues as to what to talk about.

This has been a slow and patient stalk through the Serengeti and this week she finally gave in to my evil charms. Perhaps it's my rants that I've been putting out in kickball, or maybe the awesome pirate toga I wore on Monday night, who knows. Hell for all I know she may have just run out of excuses, her friends all out of town, and thought why the hell not he doesn't seem THAT much like a serial killer. So any advice on what to talk about during the date, what I should do, proper moves and the like, I'm open to all suggestions. Except from Adam, I will not bash her in the head like a caveman and take her back to my dwelling. She is a wonderful lady and I shall treat her as such, unless this progresses and she asks me to do that one do in the form of role-playing. Then I might need Mitts to get me some fur Conan like outfits and find myself a club.

If you don't care about professional wrestling you may stop reading at this point in the story. I know it's not quite flowing like it has been the last week or so but I didn't read Hunter this morning so I'm as shall we say inspired like I usually am. I've been meaning to write about the return of the wrestling promotion that more of an effect on me then The Drive and The Fumble did in regards to football; I'm talking about E C F'N W.

As with most diehard ECW faithful, I have been hesitant about this resurrection seeing as the man with his hands in the pot is Vincent Kennedy McMahon. As much as he visionary within the business in the 80s, he single handedly killed all competition at the turn of the century. Sure WCW and ECW had died by their own hands, but SOMEONE could have bought WCW and kept it running, but this isn't the land of what ifs. McMahon bought both and the one good thing that came about is some of the best DVDs that have EVER been put out.

Now, with Vinnie Mac behind this we have all been worried that this ECW would be a washed down image of what we all knew and loved. That those hacks he calls "writers" would be given control and that HHH would have 20 segments on that show as well. This past Wednesday relieved some of those worries with the WWE vs. ECW show. It wasn't the actual matches themselves, we saw RVD wrestle a true RVD match. No, it was the commentary by Taz and Joey Styles. JR wasn't feeding lines to Joey from the back, he CALLED the match; something that I always enjoyed more then telling a story. A match should tell a story, but it shouldn't need someone to carry the match via commentary.

Now great commentary can turn an ok match into a good match, but I also think about what happens when you go to a show live. You hear no commentary, the match speaks for itself and I think it's something Joey believes in as well. If the match is crap don't put it over as "one of the greatest matches I've ever seen ladies and gentlemen." Concentrate on the match, not on some other storyline you just saw that has nothing to do with the match. I think that kind of commentary can actually HURT a match. When you don't pay attention to THAT match you hurt those who are in the ring.

It's funny that I say this, specially that in two weeks I will be entering into the commentary booth for the hottest up and coming promotion on the east coast, the Eastern Wrestling Alliance. We don't need commentary for a great show, our boys work their collective ASSES off and ALWAYS put on a great show. I have yet to go to an EWA show and not be entertained. I do hope everyone comes out June 24th to Essex, Maryland to see some damn good wrestling.

Back to the point at hand and Extreme Championship Wrestling and its return. Wednesday gave me hope that ECW will actually be ECW. I will say this, I think Vince knows that for ECW to be a success it can't seem like WWECW and thus has given Paul the reigns to this bastard of a horse. Paul is, in my opinion, the greatest booker this sport has ever known. He was able to take the land of the misfit toys from a simple bingo hall and make them the number two promotion in all of America.

I love the idea the Kurt Angle is a part of ECW I foresee him being Paul's new Taz. I have NO idea why the Big Show is a part of ECW unless he's going to be Paul's 911. I mean, who is Big Show going to be wrestling, Mikey?! Naturally there are some people I'd love to see in the new ECW, from the WWE, OVW, TNA and Indys. Other then those OFFICIALLY announced so far (meaning they have their profiles up on the ECW website or saw on the ECW roster on the show) the following is who I would put on the ECW show to fill out it's roster. These are people they actually could sign RIGHT NOW, I will follow with who I WANT to be there and may happen in time, but cannot to previous commitments.

From Raw-Charlie Haas, Johnny Parisi, Rob Conway, Val Venis.

From Smackdown-Matt Hardy, Kid Kash, James Gibson, Paul Birchall, Mexicools, Simon Dean

From OVW-CM Punk, Aaron Stevens, Amish Roadkill, Da Beast, Deuce and Domino

From Indys-Steve Corino, Lance Storm, Homicide, The Blue Meanie, Tracy Smothers

I think with those guys, plus those that we've already seen ECW would be set for a great run. Now there are few TNA guys I am NEED in ECW. Mainly because of their history and what they and Paul can do together. Namely Raven, Shane Douglas and The Dudley Boys. Hell, I can even do without the Dudleys I just NEED Raven and Shane Douglas in ECW. They were what drove ECW, not New Jack, The Sandman or even Tommy Dreamer. It was Raven and Shane Douglas, arguably the two best heels of the 90s.

Now like many I am weary of having so many WWE people involved with the actual PPV. We right now have zero true ECW matches, less you want to count Taz vs. Lawler. Though I do hear the Balls vs. Tanaka and The FBI vs. Tajiri and Crazy with Mikey will be happening as well. Personally I'd rather see The Impact Players, period. If Paul has the full reigns, this will be something special and I cannot wait.

Now, for your moment of Zen

I should probably start by apologizing right now, for as you may have guessed (if you're a part of the educated few), I was reading the good Doctor this morning, specifically Hunter S Thompsons book Songs of the Damned and thus Im in one of THOSE moods. Yes, those moods I get when I spent a lil bit of time reading the good Doctor and that side of me that sort of spills onto the page like a crazed chimpanzee on crack let loose on a shit farm. So naturally todays post may be a lil wild, a lil crazy, but hey I like that now and then, especially in the bedroom even if its been over a year since Ive been wild and crazy in a bedroom.

So then last night I received my most recent Netflix DVDs in the mail and spent the night watching the first, Paradise Lost. Ive seen part two, but Netflix was waiting on another copy of the original so I finally got to see this one. What a fucking railroad job they put on these poor kids, the filthy swine. Instead of doing real police work they decide to clean house of the unwanted in good ol god fearing West Memphis, Arkansas and arrest the kids who wore black, listened to good classical music (read Metallica, Slayer), and may have dipped into the religion known as Wicca to the masses. Instead of having any evidence, they proclaim them guilty when they arrest them and crucify them in the court of public opinion before any trial is had.

Their big piece of evidence against these kids is a confession of one of them, Jessie Misskelley, who very well could be called mentally retarded. I mean the kid has an IQ of 72, was interrogated for two and a half hours before ANYTHING was recorded. When it was recorded they more or less hold his hand through the confession. Of course the officers in charge of the interrogation cant remember what they discussed prior to the recording, just his confession. Needless to say I wouldnt mind taking a baseball bat to these fucking swines legs.

Jason Baldwin and Damien Echols (who co-wrote the song Army Reserve on the new Pearl Jam album) were tried together and the only reason they were convicted, seeing as the prosecution had ZERO evidence was the fact that they beat into the jurys head that they were devil worshippers. I think Damien said it best when he said, West Memphis is the second Salem. Apparently anything bad that happens in that town is blamed on the devil, so naturally the folks convict children who listen to the devils music. The biggest piece of work is the prosecutions occult expert. A man who had the audacity to call himself a Dr., of course he got his PhD from a mail in college and didnt attend one class to receive that or his Masters degree.

This expert on the occult was able to say that these childrens blood could not be found at the blood scene because some cults use blood or as they call it the life force apparently, and they drank it all. The only thing he said on the stand that wasnt an outright stream of bullshit was saying the Pentagram wasnt a sign of devil worship. So these kids have been jailed for life, and in the case of Damien sentenced to death, for being nothing other then different then everyone else. Its truly sad to think that in this world there are still some people so ignorant and stupid to believe that these kids had the cunning to pull off this. Of course, you look at the towns people from West Memphis and they would probably argue with you that the world is flat and the sun revolves around us.

This case every since I heard it has been a big thing to me. I will not be happy until these boys receive justice and sadly theyve been in prison now for 13 years. Damien has missed 13 years of his childs life because of this witch hunt. The only good thing is that there is a good number of people out there, celebrity and common folk alike, who want to see justice and see the West Memphis 3 freed. I know if I ever won the lottery a portion of it would be going to their defense fund to help give these men the freedom theyve long deserved.

In other news, I did attend the lovely and simply gorgeous wedding of my friend Luke and Cathy over the weekend up in PA. It is always nice to see two people so in love, and so happy with each other, join in union to live their lives as one. They have been like this since I knew them and wish them nothing but the best in their future endeavors. It was also nice to see some friends that I dont get to hang out with other then at game. Living three to four hours away doesnt exactly make it easy to go out to the bar with my buds, so this was a nice added bonus.

During the drive though, I was able to help myself with my own therapy. Long drives alone I do a good portion of thinking, most of the time for the better, some times in a far off dreamland that I like to call, what would happen if I won the lottery. So I am better, this is in regards to the previous posts I have made about my mental state concerning my love life. Everything isnt green in the garden of good and evil, but it is now partly cloudy with a slight breeze rustling through the iris and lilacs.

There was a compromise of sorts within my mental state, something suggested by a friend. A suggestion coming from this person that I never expected, especially as she is the one who hates that side of me the most, I believe hate may not even be a strong enough word for how she feels about him. So the Sidious side of me has gained ground and we agreed to share the lease on me. Hopefully he doesnt try for a complete takeover, for that war has been fought and he lost. Sadly, much like the League of Nations after World War I, I was not able to keep things secure and safe after that battle. So to make sure he doesnt pull a Germany and come back like a blitzkrieg, and understanding has been made and both sides are happy for the moment.

Does this mean that I am giving up on trying to settle down, have a respectable relationship with someone who is psycho enough to put up with the likes of me? Hardly, but seeing as that has yet to come to fruition, I see no harm in allowing to devil play in this playground. Plus, this makes me happy and not that sappy emo-esque fuck I was for a few weeks so viva la resistance.

Funny side not, I just put anti emo into the Yahoo Image search and it brought up a bunch of pictures of Anti Flag and other punk bands, rock on. Im hardcore.and Im hardcore too. Here is the proof of my claim as the new EWA Ring Announcer

I know many people have been concerned with my emotional state the last few weeks as expressed through my last three posts. Worry not for I am not turning emo, if anything I'd go on a shooting spree not cut myself and listen to crappy music. Luckily for everyone I'm no where near that homicidal. Though nothing can pick your spirits up more then taking part in something that just may be your biggest passion.

This weekend, at the EWA show in Essex, Maryland I took part of something that is a great passion. I was the EWA Ring Announcer for the evening and had a WONDERFUL time. Everyone was willing to help me out, give me pointers, and hold my hand in my first full blown Ring Announcing experience. A big thanks to Marcus Dowling who was amazing to work with and gave me flying colors.

The fans by the end of the night were even heckling me which means I must have been doing something right. A few even stopped me as I left the arena to tell me that I did a great job, though I never imagined that I would be told that my voice travels really well. I don't know if this will be a constant thing or a one timer, but we all know what I hope for. With work and finances preventing me from training to actually wrestle, this is the next best thing one could hope for. Who knows, maybe this will lead to me actually going the other route and train to be a manager.

The show itself was a great show and it was awesome seeing it that close. The DVD will be amazing I'm sure, and I'm curious to hear and see myself on the DVD.

Sunday we woke up early and went to the Nats/O's game with the HOES and had an absolute blast. We grilled, we drank, we made fun of people's signifigant others, all and all, a wonderful time was had. Some of us got toasty, others were smart and put on sunblock, but we all got ferschnikened. The Nats won the game 3-1 and won the first ever Battle of the Beltway, so up yours B-More...who is your daddy and what does he do?

As for my current emotional state, no worries. The crying is over and I feel better. I have come to grips with everything and will move along loving life as I should. As a matter of fact the final nail in that coffin comes today at kickball when everyone will be welcomed into Raven's Clockwork Orange House of Fun. I have come to terms with everything that was beating at me, keeping me down.

Though I would like to announce the creation of a new support group, Handsome Men Who Can't Get Dates or the HMWCGD. We opened with two members (Hahn and myself), declared one person inelligble for life (Matt White), and are considering the nomination of Kenny for the group. Though Hahn might be leaving the group already, he will remain here in spirit and hopefully never returns once he leaves the group. Hell, that is almost our creed, once you leave you better stay gone.

Dale Cooper: Albert, where does this attitude of general unpleasantness come from? Albert Rosenfield: I'll have to get back to you on that.
For the last two weeks I have been attempting to come out of whatever this funk is. Is it depression or is a part of me just getting anxious about some unforseen event that is to come and I don't want to trudge through those events without some hottie by my side. I mean hell, Ash had hotties at his side as he shot and chopped up Deadites. For me all I seem to have lately is the Zombie Survival Guide to keep me warm at night.
So let me expand on yesterday as it apparently confused people. Go back to the Not EMO post from last week, re-read it. Notice the section in there about Won't, that is who yesterday's post was in reference to. Things started to turn away from what I thought was going to happen and they were looking up. I was beginning to get out of the funk and feel like myself again, and then I happened. I mentioned something about the current boyfriend that got her thinking and BAM, here I am again. Do I feel stupid for it, eh maybe a lil bit, but I know in the long run this is the right path for her to take.
Yes I understand that it's a blessing and a curse to be able to look at a situation from an un-biased perspective and give advice on it. Why else would I give advice that would bury me, unless under everything I am Masochistic which is probably true. Hell, let us take a look at being Masochistic-
Self-defeating Personality Disorder is a pervasive pattern of self-defeating behavior, beginning by early adulthood and present in a variety of contexts. The person may often avoid or undermine pleasurable experiences, be drawn to situations or relationships in which he or she will suffer, and prevent others from helping him or her, as indicated by at least five of the following:
* chooses people and situations that lead to disappointment, failure, or mistreatment even when better options are clearly available;
* rejects or renders ineffective the attempts of others to help him of her;
* following positive personal events (e.g., new achievement), responds with depression, guilt, or a behavior that produces pain ( e.g., an accident);
* incites angry or rejecting responses from others and then feels hurt, defeated, or humiliated (e.g., makes fun of spouse in public, provoking an angry retort, then feels devastated);
* rejects opportunities for pleasure, or is reluctant to acknowledge enjoying himself or herself (despite having adequate social skills and the capacity for pleasure);
* fails to accomplish tasks crucial to his or her personal objectives despite demonstrated ability to do so, (e.g., helps fellow students write papers , but is unable to write his or her own);
* is uninterested in or rejects people who consistently treat him or her well, (e.g., is not attracted to caring sexual partners);
* engages in excessive self-sacrifice that is unsolicited by the intended recipients of the sacrifice;
The behaviors do not occur exclusively in response to, or in anticipation of , being physically, sexually, or psychologically abused.
The behaviors do not occur only when the person is depressed.
Hell, I never read all the things before....yeah that pretty much seals the deal then, I'm Masochistic. A point for the psychiatrist within me, saves me a bunch of money on my car insurance as well, well probably not, but it would be a lot cooler if it did. So now that I have properly diagnosed myself as being Masochistic, what now? Just to clarify, this is not the S&M type of Masochistic, this is the emotional mental type.
Here's the deal, I can realize this about myself which I guess puts me a step ahead of some people with similar issues the question is, what can I do about it? Right about now all I want to do is go and hide and get away from everyone. That all this pain and sadness and the feeling of defeet will just go away if I stop socializing with everyone. If I keep to myself I don't have to see a happy couple walking down the street holding hands, or friends looking into each other's eyes, so in love.
This however isn't a healthy option, what do I just go out and buy World of Warcraft and escape the world? Sadly this isn't a time where I could just jump on a horse and travel the lands as an unknown, living off what I hunt, and forgetting everything and everyone in my past. To go out like my namesake and just wander the vast openess that is the southwest and rocky mountains. Though as Eric has mentioned, I can't do this, it's not healthy.
Yes, I know it's not, doesn't mean I still don't want to do it. Maybe just roam the Pacific Northwest, in those beautiful Canadian Forests. Hell, if I won the lottery, even if it was only for a few million, I could do it, and I just might. Just buy or build a log cabin up in the woods and live the rest of my days alone without any social expectation to be with someone. I love my family and I'm sure I would visit them once or year or something, but I just....it's getting to the point where I can't take this anymore.
If something is going to happen to this world I cannot wait any longer. Every day this world gets more and more disgusting. The sides are getting more and more polarized to the point where it's becoming down right unbearble. I don't know anymore, the fight is just being sucked out of me at this point.
I think one problem is that there used to be so much hope inside of me. For everything and everyone, there was so much hope. I know that right there is what led to my downfall, the hope that maybe this one would be different, that she would stay around or that I wouldn't drive them away. I have hoped and all it has done brought me pain in the end...I'm officially all out of hope.

I just had a long post written up, but something happened and the window closed, bastards. The long and short of it, yeah I think I can summarize. -Felt better after the theraputic post -Thought I was wrong about one of the topics -Shot myself in the foot and thus was right about all of the topics -Except for the failed Mormon relationship, I've been batting .000 since Jan 05 -Trying out for the ring announcer position for the EWA -So fed up want to become Jeremiah Johnson and live off the land So there you have it, everything that should have been in the post, but quickly summarized without the bullshit. I feel like the flowers in ghostbusters and the table cloth was just taken out of me. Just no clue anymore, no idea what to do, recluse looks to be a better idea each day as the sun sets.
Yes, I know this isn't a good option, but I try to distract myself and it isn't working. This depression or whatever it is is even effecting how I feel when I go to the gym. Life sucks, I'm wearing my helmet and trying to make myself as happy as possible, I just can't find much to be happy about nowadays.

I could never be emo mainly for the reason that I have zero desire to hurt myself physically, listen to crappy music, and I plain just don't have the hair for it. No, I guess it's about that time of the year where I post a woe is me writing. I am honestly going to attempt to not sound like I screaming WHAT ABOUT ME?! WHAT ABOUT RAVEN?!
It's about the time where I make a post of going, why not me, everyone else is happy, everyone else has found someone, why not me when everyone says I'm such a great guy. I've made that post plenty of times over the years and for the last year or two I've been pretty good about not posting it. I've managed to keep myself happy one way or another, even if I was single and celibate. I've grown to be happy with who I am and I believe that is more important then what car you drive, your bank account, or who you know.
I've attempted to live life with the Bene Gesserit mantra with me, Fear is the mind killer and all that. The good news is it is not that I fear being alone like I once did. Growing up my greatest fear, and probably still is it just doesn't control me anymore, was growing old alone. Perhaps that is why at a young age I connect with James T Kirk cause I believed as he did, that I would die alone.
I do believe I know where all of these feelings as of late have been coming from, weddings. I attended three weddings prior to this year, two when I was little to not care and one where I was afraid that the rere with the banjo was going to make an appearance. In the last month I have attended two and have one more in a few weeks. Thus thrusting upon me the important message of you must have someone to be happy. I know this is not true but I would be lying if I said it wasn't a lil bit depressing going to these weddings and being one of the only single people there.
Perhaps we all just have these clocks imbedded into us that tell us when we should be doing certain things that society expects of us. Course it could stem from a long running thing in my life that I've had since I was younger. When I was a child all I wanted was to coach football, have a wife, kids, and live a happy life. Now I know life sucks and I need to wear a fucking helmet, but I believe the weddings have merely brought that back in me.
I've been in love love three times in my life. When I say love love I mean the kind of love where you would gladly spend the rest of your life with that person. I've been in love more then those times but it wasn't a forever kind of love and now I'm sounding like some 80's power ballad. The first one; well that was no one's fault but the fates. The second is the bitch we do not speak of, actually we can I don't really care anymore about Beth. I no longer let the fear of her run my life like she did for so many years. That situation was no one's fault but my own and I can readily admit that. The third was merely the circumstances at the moment did not allow it to happen, shit happens ya know.
Now I look at my current "love life" and boy, is that convoluted and complicated. Three people and we shall describe them as Shouldn't, Won't and Doubtful.
Shouldn't is a great person, a truly beautiful soul who would treat me like a king. Sounds great, many people are all for it, but honestly the problem is me. I know deep down I'm not the person who should be with her as I will probably end up breaking her heart cause I'm an idiot like that. Yes, there are reasons why I probably would break her heart; I just know that I am the wrong person for her. I know certain people will disagree with me on it, but I don't want to hurt her, that's how beautiful she is.
Won't, someone that flirting and some kissing have been going on since last year. Well, one kissing incident until this season at least. Personally, I think things could be great with her, maybe even surpass some things I've had in the past. But as is always the case with my luck, there's catch but then again there always is. It comes in the form of a boyfriend, who currently isn't in the country at the moment. Yes, I've been good, I haven't done anything carnal with the lady, and our self restraint has been on the level of gods one might say. I know she has to figure things our within her, like is this only because she's lonely and needs SOMETHING or is it more then that. Well, I know my luck in matters of whatever and thus it tells me that it is only time until she decides on he who is not here, and I can't blame her for that.
Doubtful, god what is it now nine years and counting? Actually this month will mark the nine year anniversary of the last time I actually saw her. She would be the first love I mentioned before. So why do I say doubtful, cause I learn from history. So many times it seemed like this was going to be it, that all the obstacles were going to fall away and just maybe the fates would give us another shot, only to be tripped up by some bullshit or another. Part of me is tired of feeling like a bloody yo-yo, part of me wonders if I only stay around because it's that hope beyond hope, and the other part wonders if I'm nothing more then a glutton for punishment.
So yes, I feel lost a bit. All my life I've felt alone, this I know. That line from Titanic the whole being in a crowded room with people screaming at the top of my lungs and no one hears, I've felt like that the majority of my life. Now I usually just attribute this to being so different from everyone else. The possibility of having to do things in the future if anything comes about (Jase and Judith know what I'm talking about) it comes with the territory I suppose. Maybe that's why I actually enjoy Superman, in a world full of people who love him but at the same time he's all alone. In many ways my room is my fortress of solitude, actually that would be a cool way to decorate my room, I wonder how I could do that.
At any rate, yes, I feel lost in matters of the heart. I'm not out there searching, I know they say just be patient and wait. Well, I've waited, I've been patient. I've seen my friends, my brothers, find two women who complete them so much it's scary. Even if one is trying to deny it and the other almost knows, it's a great feeling for me to see those two happy. I never EVER would have thought that about the one, no one could of predicting him settling down like he has, down right shocking.
You may wonder why I put a picture of Cyclops up, well in my mind's eye that's how I look to myself when I feel like this. Yeah, I know I don't have that much hair, I could only wish, but I think you can see that look in his face. Which is why don't be surprised if I become something of a hermit in the coming weeks, months, who knows how long. Yeah, I know it solves nothing, but it also gives me no reminders of what I don't have either. I can do what I said I would do, concentrate on my body and nutrition. I can expand my knowledge with reading which really translates into my beer money could buy an X-Box 360. I just may need to get away from everything for awhile.
Now for one person reading this who may be wondering, yes, HE tried coming out a week or two ago. When I saw two of the three in one night, he crept to the surface to give a grin and a laugh, but he was quickly repressed back down. He will not come out again, that part of my life is over. I know how much some of my friends hate that side of me and I hate that side of me to an extent and he will not take over.
So there you have it, I got it out of my system. I've been trying to write this for about two weeks now, I just haven't been able to get it out. What's to happen, not even the wisest can say. All I can really do is what is right for my life and what makes me happy. I am not searching and maybe I won't even socialize much. I am not one who takes failure very well and I guess in the end that's how I feel about my love life, a failure. The important thing for though is to not fear, I no longer fear being alone and I suppose that is a step in the right direction.

I sit here at work, my last rotation at this job until I go to a job that will be much easier, closer to home and did I mention a regular work schedule, sick out of my gourd and only here because if I wasn't come May 1st I'd be broke for some time. I can only come to one conclusion; Castle Greyskull infected me with the HIV.

I am currently breathing through gills that my body has adapted for I can no longer breathe through normal means. No, I have not become an Atlantean like Namor, I just have a cold that is trying to slowly choke the life out of me. This on top of two hours of sleep after I roared down the highway from Greyskull like a bat from hell and managed to get from Easton, PA to Alexandria, VA in 3 hours. So two hours of sleep a head cold like a mother has me feeling about as well as Dubya's approval rating.

The only thing one can hope for at this, besides a lapdance from the Stratus Sisters as Mickie James looks on, is that this clears up by my flight Weds evening. That is not my idea of a swell trip, specially when there's a wedding to be had. Speaking of the wedding, going to my sister's rehearsal dinner as Rowdy Roddy Piper, too much?

So of course the big news of the weekend was Wrestlemania....or not. The BIG news of the weekend was the return to the squared circle of Lance FREAKIN Storm. Perhaps the most underrated wrestler of his generation he came back this weekend took on Bryan Danielson for MY World Heavyweight Title, the Ring of Honor strap. Apparently they had an amazing match and Danielson won by submission after 26 minutes. Even better is the fact that the entire show apparently is considered by all who were there as one of the best ROH shows of ALL TIME. It without a doubt was the best show IN CHICAGO THAT WEEKEND.

So here I am, hoping that Gabe and his people start to bust their ass right now to get this put together before the April 22nd show so when I go to Philly that day I can leave with that DVD in hand more excited then a virgin with a slutty prom date. I can't express how excited I am to see two of my favorite workers, period, against each other in what could be nothing short of classic.

Now, onto Wrestlemania. Apparently the opinion depends on the coast you live on. The West Coast apparently thought it rivaled Mania 2000 with the suckage. I, however, enjoyed the majority of it. I thought every match but the Boogeyman, Pillow Fight (without pillows apparently), and the main event were good solid matches. You had your spot fests of Money In The Bank and Cactus Jack. You had great psychological traditional matches in the US and Woman's title match. The Tag was better then I expected it to be, the World Heavyweight match was given to short of time. Personally I think it should have been a three way dance ECW style, but that's just my opinion.

Now the obvious problems of this pay per view were as follows. No MNM or Cruiserweight matches, even though they have the ability to downright steal the show. You put JR on commentary, should I get a bucket? The only time I found it pleasing to the ears was when Joey Styles was doing commentary. You have a pillow fight, yet not once was a pillow used. I love to see Candice Michelle as much as the next walking hard on, but this had to be a match? Could we not see MNM vs. London and Kendrick or The Mexicools or Kash and Knoble? Hell I would have settled for yet another cruiserweight battle royal, anything but that atrocity.

Now, the so called main event of the evening. It's truly sad when the only promising thing about this match was the entrances. One for maybe the coolest fucking entrance in the history of mankind, better then even Flair coming in on a helicopter. HHH's whole Conan throne getup deal was fucking money. The only way he could have topped it was if he was able to take that giant hammer from the chair to the ring. Now Cena's entrance got a HUGE pop from me, and no not because he gave the NRA a big boost and it definitely wasn't for John Cena himself. Oh no, it was for CM Punk being live and in living color as one of the "gangstas" in his hometown, constantly on camera. That got the biggest pop from me all night I think, even bigger then The Million Dollar Man doing the basketball trick to Eugene.

All in all I'll give it a 6.5-7 out of 10 for a show. There were some good solid things in it, and then there were some things that just make you wonder what the fuck were they thinking when they came up with this garbage. Now, onto my favorite parts of the night in chronological order. Shelton's running ladder plancha
Ric Flair taking a suplex off the top rope
Shelton's Spiderman jump out of nowhere
JBL/Benoit Finish
The Entire Edge/Jack match
Taker Powerbomb off the top rope
Taker with a suicide dive off the top rope
UNDERTAKER TOMBSTONED MARK HENRY WITH EASE!!!
HBK whipping Vince in the chest with a belt
The DX Chop
The Insane elbow drop from the biggest ladder ever
The Entire Mickie Trish match, especially the modified Camel Clutch
The three person German suplex
I think that about ended it, oh wait; the FUCK YOU CENA chants were gold.
